dc_title_s: South America, Colombia--west coast, approaches to Bahía de Buenaventura (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From Colombian charts 1990 to 1999." Place names in Spansh with English glossary. "Copyright 2004 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." 'Copyright restrictions of the country of origin continue to exist." "Soundings in meters." Shipping list no.: 2009-0007-S. Includes source diagram and tidal information. Map no.22051. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency. (2004). South America, Colombia--west coast, approaches to Bahía de Buenaventura (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/cb240dw7799 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
